## Content Strategy

### The Mix

- **70% Craft & Expertise** — research insights, usability findings, methodology takes, process reveals, opinions on how UX actually works. Builds reputation with other designers and with the people who hire them.
- **15% Personal / Behind the work** — career turns, the research session that didn't go as planned, honest observations about what the job is really like. Humanizes without dominating.
- **15% Conversion** — job-search posts, client offers, portfolio drops. Direct asks, done right.

### Post Types

| Type | Job | Frequency |
|------|-----|-----------|
| **Authority** | Show craft and point of view | 2 of every 3 posts |
| **Visibility** | Reach new people with story or relatable take | 1 of every 3 posts |
| **Conversion** | Direct ask — job or client | Max 1× per 2 weeks |

UX designers should lean on specificity. A single user quote, one usability finding, one decision that got reversed because of research — these are more compelling than broad claims about UX maturity or design thinking.

